Jenkins Assignment

Module-8: Jenkins Assignment - 1
You have been asked to:
● Trigger a pipeline using Git when push on Develop branch
● Pipeline should pull git content to a folder

Module-8: Jenkins Assignment - 2
You have been asked to:
● Add 2 nodes to Jenkins master
● Create 2 jobs with the following jobs:
○ Push to test
○ Push to prod
● Once a push is made to test branch copy git files to test server
● Once a push is made to master branch copy git files to prod server 

Module-8: Jenkins Assignment - 3
You have been asked to:
● Create a pipeline in jenkins
● Once push is made to “develop” branch in git, trigger job “test”. This will copy git files to
test node
● If test job is successful, then prod job should be triggered
● Prod jobs should copy files to prod node



Step-1
Login to AWS – launch 3 Instances (Ubuntu) One Master Two Slaves – Open port 8080
Step-2
Login to Master – Update the OS – Install Java-21 – Install Jenkins – Install and Initialize Git – Install SSH
Perform below Commands to complete Step-2
1.	Sudo apt update –y
2.	sudo apt install openjdk-21-jdk –y
3.	java –version
4.	export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-21-openjdk-amd64
5.	export PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH
6.	Follow The link to Install Jenkins ( https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/installing/linux/ )
7.	Follow The link to Install Jenkins Install and Initialize Git  ( https://github.com/P-r-a-t-i-k-D/Git_Assingment )
8.	sudo apt install openssh-server -y
9.	sudo systemctl enable ssh
10.	sudo systemctl start ssh





Step-3
Goto Master and create 3 branches (Develop, Test, Prod) – Push to GitHub

Step–4
Goto Slave 1 and 2 and Install Java and SSH

Step -5
Login to Jenkins – Goto Settings  - Security - TCP port for inbound agents (Random) – Save – Back to Jenkins Home – Click on New Item – Give Name -  Choose Freestyle Project – Ok – Write Description - Source Code Management (Git) – Give Repo URL – Specify Branch – Triggers (GitHub hook trigger for GITScm polling) – Save

Step-6
Goto – Settings – Nodes – New Node – Give Name - Write Description - Remote root directory (/home/ubuntu/jenkins) – Give Labels - Launch method (Launch agents via SSH) – Host (Give Slave 1 Private IP) – Credentials – Add (Click on Jenkins) – Kind (SSH Username with private key) – Give User Name - Private Key – Select Enter Directly – Paste Slave1 PEM Key here - Host Key Verification Strategy (Non verifying Verification Strategy) – Availability (Keep this agent online as much as possible) – Save

Step-7
Goto – Settings – Nodes – New Node – Give Name - Write Description - Remote root directory (/home/ubuntu/jenkins) – Give Labels - Launch method (Launch agents via SSH) – Host (Give Slave 2 Private IP) – Credentials – Add (Click on Jenkins) – Kind (SSH Username with private key) – Give User Name - Private Key – Select Enter Directly – Paste Slave2 PEM Key here - Host Key Verification Strategy (Non verifying Verification Strategy) – Availability (Keep this agent online as much as possible) – Save

Step-8
Goto Jenkins Home – Click on New Item – Give Name - Write Description – Click on Restrict where this project can be run - Label Expression (Give the node’s lebel1 name where job will run) - Source Code Management (Git) – Give Repository URL – Credentials (ubuntu) – Specify Branch – Triggers (Build after other projects are built
) – Select Projects to watch – Specify Project – Save

Step-9
Goto Jenkins Home – Click on New Item – Give Name - Write Description – Click on Restrict where this project can be run - Label Expression (Give the node’s lebel2 name where job will run) - Source Code Management (Git) – Give Repository URL – Credentials (ubuntu) – Specify Branch – Triggers (Build after other projects are built
) – Select Projects to watch – Specify Project – Save

Step-10
Goto Jenkins Home – Select Plugins - Available plugins – Download SSH and Build Pipeline Plugins
Step-8
Goto Jenkins Home – Click on + Icon (New View) – Give Name – Type (Build Pipeline View) – Create - Write Description – Give Build Pipeline View Title - Select Initial Job – Save – Add Step by Step



 

